The 46th edition of the Concours d Elegance, was held at the Ngong Racecourse, Nairobi on Sunday.The event which is one of the biggest in the Kenya Motor Sports Federation calendar, attracted a crowd of over 10,000 motorists and their families to cheer participants who were battling it out in various categories.The annual series organised by the Alfa Romeo Owners Club was sponsored by Commercial Bank of Africa.Italian Ambassador Mauro Massoni and CBA s CEO Jeremy Ngunze were among those present.Mohamed Paruez was the overall winner for the Jaguar Mark 5 1950 entry.